  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.polymtl.inf3995.oronos.services.RestHttpWrapper

  • public class RestHttpWrapper
extends java.lang.Object

    Rest Http Wrapper

    Singleton Rest Http Wrapper that is the entry and departure point for any rest/http communication with the server.
    Since:
    2018-04-12
    Version:
    0.0
    Author:
    Fabrice Charbonneau, Charles Hosson

      • setLoginInfo

        public void setLoginInfo(java.lang.String serverIp,
                         int port,
                         java.lang.String username,
                         java.lang.String password)
        This method is useful to set the server url, the username and the password that will be sent to the server.
        Parameters:
        serverIp - IP address of the server.
        port - Port number of the server.
        username - Username the client wish to log in as.
        password - Password associated to the username.

      • sendPostUsersLogin

        public void sendPostUsersLogin(com.android.volley.Response.Listener<java.lang.Void> resListen,
                               com.android.volley.Response.ErrorListener errListen)
        This method attempts to log in a user with the information provided to the Rest Http Wrapper using the setLoginInfo. Therefore, setLoginInfo() method should be called at least once before trying to sendPostUsersLogin().
        Parameters:
        resListen - the listener waiting for the response.
        errListen - the listener waiting for any error response that could be sent.

      • sendPostUsersLogout

        public void sendPostUsersLogout(com.android.volley.Response.Listener<java.lang.Void> resListen,
                                com.android.volley.Response.ErrorListener errListen)
        This method attempts to log out a user with the information provided to the Rest Http Wrapper using the setLoginInfo. Therefore, setLoginInfo() method should be called at least once before trying to sendPostUsersLogout(). It is not mandatory to sendPostUsersLogin() before, but if no user has been logged in previously, the log out will do nothing even if sent.
        Parameters:
        resListen - the listener waiting for the response.
        errListen - the listener waiting for any error response that could be sent.

      • sendPostUsersHeartbeat

        public void sendPostUsersHeartbeat(com.android.volley.Response.Listener<java.lang.Void> resListen,
                                   com.android.volley.Response.ErrorListener errListen)
        This method signals to the server the client is still up and running. If no heartbeat is heard from the client by the server, the server will eventually close any socket related to the client.
        Parameters:
        resListen - the listener waiting for the response.
        errListen - the listener waiting for any error response that could be sent.

      • sendJsonGetRequest

        private void sendJsonGetRequest(java.lang.String url,
                                com.android.volley.Response.Listener<org.json.JSONObject> resListener,
                                com.android.volley.Response.ErrorListener errListener)
        This method is a template for any Json Get Request; it formats the url by adding the specific part of any request to the general «root» part of the server url. Then, it sends the request.
        Parameters:
        url - the specific part of a get request to the server.
        resListener - the listener waiting for the response.
        errListener - the listener waiting for any error response that could be sent.
